    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="307"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d307">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to Prime
                        Minister <persName type="to">Churchill</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d307fn1">Sent to the United States Naval Attaché, London,
                        via Navy channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-30">30 July
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For the <gloss target="#t_FNP1">Former Naval Person</gloss> from the President
                    personal and secret. Number 335.</p>
                <p>Your number 390.<note n="2" xml:id="d307fn2">Not printed. In this message
                        Churchill had informed Roosevelt of the sinking of three enemy submarines in
                        the Bay of Biscay.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Grand hunting in the Bay of Biscay. We got one too off Recife, Brazil. We still
                    need <gloss target="#t_Lifebelt1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lifebelt</hi>
                    </gloss> nevertheless.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
